The primary colors are the three colors that can be combined in different proportions to create all other colors. The traditional primary colors are red, blue, and yellow. These colors are often used in art, design, and printing as the base colors for mixing and creating a wide range of other colors. In the world of light, the primary colors are red, blue, and green, which can be combined in different proportions to create all other colors in the visible spectrum. This is known as the additive color model and is used in technologies such as televisions and computer monitors.